The paper deals with the problem of learning from distributed data, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The focus is on the agnostic setting, which involves dealing with arbitrary forms of noise, making it relevant to the areas of distributed computing (cs.DC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information theory (cs.IT).
